description:
&lt;p&gt;Matron for Maternity Services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you aspire to deliver the Best Possible Maternity Care every time?&lt;/strong&gt; That’s the approach to Maternity Services at Northampton General Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why come to Team NGH?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Maternity services include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A modern alongside 3 bed Birth Centre with birthing pools and 8 postnatal beds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8 bed consultant-led Labour Ward with a birthing pool.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A dedicated Obstetric theatre with recovery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;18 bed Maternity Higher Observation Ward&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Bereavement Suite with garden&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Maternity Day Unit and Outpatient Clinic and Midwifery Led Sonography services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;25 bedded ward for inpatient antenatal and postnatal mothers and babies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A dedicated and award winning dedicated Home Birth Team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With a current delivery rate of 4700 births and ambitious plans across the Local Maternity System for transforming maternity services to be aligned with the Better Births recommendations, this is an exciting time and a great opportunity for you to come and join our innovative and award winning maternity team. Just a flavor of some of the reasons you may want to come to and join Team NGH;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are forward thinking and innovative in our redesign of services for women: being nominated for a PENNA Award in 2018 for our Meet the Matron Clinic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We have a successful Midwifery Safeguarding team winning the Nursing Times Award 2016 for Enhancing Patient dignity, and a PENNA in 2016 for Improving experiences of people with Disability. Shortlisted for Enhancing patient care Nursing Times Awards and the RCM Awards in 2017 for Excellence in Maternity Care. Finalists in two categories for the 2017 PENNA for Personalisation of care and Continuity of carer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are passionate AND innovative in our approach in designing support and wellbeing for staff; winning the Iolanthe Midwifery Award in 2018 and having a senior full time lead for A-EQUIP.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive in developing the workforce for the future, this year saw the first ever Florence Nightingale Midwifery Scholar.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We deliver some of the most highly rated maternity care experience in the UK: the recent CQC Maternity Experience survey showed that Northampton is performing better than most UK hospitals and in five survey questions was rated the best in the UK.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We have Full BFI accreditation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We could go on……&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a senior experienced, dynamic, high performing midwife to join the team as a Matron for Maternity Services. We are looking for a clinically credible midwife with a broad range of midwifery experience and exceptional clinical ability. We need someone who possesses strong clinical leadership and who has excellent communication and networking skills, able to support the maternity team on our Journey to Outstanding. You will need to be self -motivated, enthusiastic and have a distinct passion for maternity services and a drive for continuous improvement in maternity safety and experience. Northampton is progressive in career development for Matrons as part of your role; you will have the opportunity to be supported to aspire to be a future Head of Midwifery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is a challenging one, but one that you will be supported in and your personal and professional growth will be encouraged and developed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a five day a week post, with on call commitment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE NOTE&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date – Thursday 3 December 2020 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Lorraine Ryan, Job title: Deputy Head of Midwifery, Email address: lorraine.ryan@ngh.nhs.uk, Telephone number: 07743600728,  Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hannah Billingham - PA to Senior Midwifery Team&lt;/p&gt;
